  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH Response to COVID-19 in the Western Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The first positive case of COVID-19 in Afghanistan was confirmed on 24 February by the Ministry of Public Health (MoPH). Since then, the pace of spread has grown steadily, with fears there may be a rapid increase soon, putting significant strain on the already stretched health system in the country. Preventing the spread of COVID-19 is the most critical need in Afghanistan, particularly among villages at highest risk in Herat, Badghis and Ghor Provinces.


In order to ensure that &#x201C;lives are saved in the areas of highest need&#x201D; (HRP Strategic Objective one), WVI proposes interventions that will provide WASH assistance to prevent community spread in priority COVID-19 districts in Herat, Badghis and Ghor Provinces.  This will be done by increasing public knowledge and practices around preventative hygiene measures through the distribution of targeted COVID-19 hand washing kits and hygiene promotion over the course of four months. Hygiene promotion will focus on regular hand washing with soap at the five critical times and on returning home, in alignment with Global WASH Cluster COVID-19 messaging.  Additional MoPH COVID-19 messaging on other transmission-reducing behaviors will be provided.  WVI will also conduct daily chlorine disinfection of at-risk public locations to further reduce the risk of transmission.</narrative>
  </description>
